Our aim is to perform meta-level tracking of a target moving confined to a roadmap. We model the roadmap as a directed, weighted graph G with vertices V , edges E and weights L
G = {V,E, L}
The set of vertices V = {v1, v2, . . . , vn} denotes the n road intersections. The set of edges E = {evivj |vi, vj ∈ V } denotes the roads on the roadmap. The set of weights L = {l(evivj )|evivj ∈ E} denotes lengths of the roads. Define a function θ on both vertices V and edges E. θ(evivj ),∀evivj ∈ E denotes the angle of road evivj with respect to a reference coordinate and θ(vm),∀vm ∈ V denotes the set of angles of roads that intersect at the vertex vm. The directed, weighted graph for the roadmap in Fig. 1 is presented in Fig. 5.
